{
  "texts": [
    "A new policy-based data collection strategy known as match and action (M&A) is proposed herein.",
    "M&A builds a unified data collection mechanism based on the data plane to avoid missed or repeated collection, which adapts to the cloudification trend with flexible deployment and good scalability.",
    "Specifically, data operation/data control (DO/DC) allocates match tables and action sets to nodes equipped with data agents (DAs) and allows the data source to execute data ingestion.",
    "The raw ingested data can be preprocessed, filtered, relayed, and analyzed with respect to file, event, network element (NE), and flow by the DAs based on the action sets defined during data transmission.",
    "In this regard, M&A pronounces an advantage in data collection, filtering, and processing for 6G data services."
  ]
}